  "text": "The different types of malaria normally found around the world and they are Plasmodium falciparum, Plasmodium vivox, Plasmodium ovale, and Plasmodium malariae [14] . In malarial blood pathologists look for red cells, white cell, parasites in different stages of life, immature and mature trophozoites, schizonts and gametocytes. It is difficult to differentiate between various stages, but S. Raviraja et al. [CITATION_1] contributed for identification of different stages based on color, shape and size. But due to use of statistical approach results are not up to the mark.",
